From Michael S Kluskens Subject Re Quadra SCSI Problems In article Mark Nodine wrote In article Bill Johnston writes In article Mark Nodine writes I don't know about the specific problem mentioned in your message but I definitely had SCSI problems between my and my venerable Jasmine Megadrive cartridge stuff deleted I doubt this is a Quadra specific I had to get rid of my venerable Bernoulli last year with enough stuff deleted might fix the problem in my case the cartridges wouldn't format mount partition for A All I know is that the Megadrives worked perfectly on both my Mac Plus and my Powerbook It was for this reason I assumed the problem had something to do with the Even with the Quadra they mostly worked The problem occurred when I ejected a cartridge from a drive it would start popping up dialog boxes saying This cartridge must be formatted with Jasmine Driveware even though there was no cartridge in the Mark The problem mentioned last is a known Quadra SCSI problem it was heavily discussed last year and an Apple employee pointed out that there was a one byte error in the SCSI driver routine for the Quadra's at least the and System should not have that problem for most people the solution was to get an updated driver from the drive In my case MASS Microsystems wrote a new driver which fixed the problem on my Quadra all that occured early last Michael Kluskens Opinions expressed are the author's and not those of his